subSubSection.paragraph:
Thorax yellow, with brownish setae. Legs yellow, with brownish setae; coxae, trochanter and femora slightly paler. Wings (
Fig. 1
) elliptical, slightly yellowish brown, with pterostigmatic areas creamy yellow. Forewing with distal margin brown and with distinct brown markings on gradate crossveins as well as on 1 r-rs; other less distinct brown markings present on distal branching points of most longitudinal veins. Veins yellowish brown except for those in dark markings brown. Hindwing much paler than forewing, with distal dark edging much shorter and paler than that on forewing. Veins pale yellow, with 1 r-rs and 2 r-rs brown.

Abdomen yellow, dorsally largely tinged with pale reddish brown. Tergite 9 and sternite 9 fused into a ring-like structure; tergite 9 (
Fig. 5
) anteriorly truncate and posteriorly broadly concaved in dorsal view; sternite 9 (
Fig. 6
) posteriorly protruding medially. Gonocoxite 9 (
Figs. 3–6
) robust on proximal half and strongly incurved on distal half, with a small hairy tubercle on inner surface; gonostylus 9 (
Figs. 4–6
) terminally flattened and bearing a spinous lobe. Ectoproct (
Figs. 3–5
) broad, directed posteroventrad, and concaved medially on posterior margin, with median portion slightly domed dorsad in lateral view, and with posterolateral corner protruding into a digitiform process. Complex of gonocoxite+gonostylus+gonapophysis 10 (
Fig. 4
) proximally broad, bearing a roundly tapered dorsal lobe and slender ventral lobe, distally with a long and blade-like projection; distal projections crossing each other at mid-length. Gonocoxite 11 invisible; gonostyli 11 (
Fig. 5
) as posteriorly bifurcated sclerite. Hypandrium internum invisible.

Tergite 8 (
Fig. 7
) short, elongated ventrad, in lateral view posteroventral corner rounded. Fused gonocoxites 8 (
Figs. 7–8
) about twice as long as tergite 8 , flatly and roundly plate-like, with posterior portion feebly sclerotized. Gonapophyses 8 (
Fig. 8
) subtriangular, largely covered by gonocoxite 8 , lateral margins distinctly sclerotized. Tergite 9 (
Fig. 7
) rather narrow dorsad, but strongly widened ventrad, with a short spinous internal ridge. Gonocoxite 9 (
Fig. 7
) narrowly foliate, almost vertically directed, with a reduced, flat and ovoid gonostylus bearing a tuft of hairs. Ectoproct short, subtrapezoidal in lateral view. Bursa copulatrix (
Figs. 7–8
) comprising a large and arcuate sclerotized sclerite, which is nearly as long as gonocoxite 8 .

